The '''Vella Lavella monarch''' ('''''Symposiachrus nigrotectus'''''), is a [[passerine]] bird in the monarch flycatcher family [[Monarchidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the islands of [[Ranongga]] and [[Vella Lavella]] in the [[Solomon Islands (archipelago)|Solomon Islands archipelago]]. It was formerly considered as [[conspecific]] with the [[Kolombangara monarch]].

==Taxonomy==
The Vella Lavella monarch was [[species description|formally described]] in 1908 by the German ornithologist [[Ernst Hartert]] based on a specimen collected on the island of [[Vella Lavella]] in the [[Solomon Islands (archipelago)|Solomon Islands archipelago]]. He coined the [[trinomial name]] ''Monarcha brodiei nigrotectus'', where ''Monarcha brodiei'' [[Edward Pierson Ramsay|Ramsay, EP]], 1879 is a [[junior synonym]] of ''Monarcha barbatus barbatus'' Ramsay, EP, 1879, the [[Solomons monarch]].<ref>{{ cite journal | last=Hartert | first=Ernst | author-link=Ernst Hartert | date=1908 | title=Dr. Hartert exhibited and described examples of the following new forms from the Solomon Islands | journal=Bulletin of the British Ornithologists' Club | volume=21 | page=105-107 [107] | url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/32426855 }}</ref><ref>{{ cite book | editor1-last=Mayr | editor1-first=Ernst | editor1-link=Ernst Mayr | editor2-last=Cottrell | editor2-first=G. William | year=1986 | title=Check-list of Birds of the World | volume=11 | publisher=Museum of Comparative Zoology | place=Cambridge, Massachusetts | page=511 | url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/14484212 }}</ref> The Vella Lavella monarch is now placed in the genus ''[[Symposiachrus]]''. It was previously considered to be a [[subspecies]] of the [[Kolombangara monarch]] (''Symposiachrus browni'') but is now treated as a separate species based on differences in plumage and DNA sequences.<ref name=ioc>{{cite web| editor1-last=Gill | editor1-first=Frank | editor1-link=Frank Gill (ornithologist) | editor2-last=Donsker | editor2-first=David | editor3-last=Rasmussen | editor3-first=Pamela | editor3-link=Pamela C. Rasmussen | date=August 2024 | title=Monarchs | work=IOC World Bird List Version 14.2 | url=https://www.worldbirdnames.org/bow/monarchs/ | publisher=International Ornithologists' Union | access-date=20 September 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1=Andersen | first1=M.J. | last2=Hosner | first2=P.A. | last3=Filardi | first3=C.E. | last4=Moyle | first4=R.G. | date=2015 | title=Phylogeny of the monarch flycatchers reveals extensive paraphyly and novel relationships within a major Australo-Pacific radiation | journal=Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution | volume=83 | pages=118–136 | doi=10.1016/j.ympev.2014.11.010| pmid=25463752 | bibcode=2015MolPE..83..118A }}</ref> The specific epithet ''nigrotectus'' combines the [[Latin]] ''niger'' meaning "black" with ''tectus'' meaning "covered" or "concealed".<ref>{{ cite web | last=Jobling | first=James A. | title=nigrotectus | work=The Key to Scientific Names | url=https://birdsoftheworld.org/bow/key-to-scientific-names/search?q=nigrotectus | publisher=Cornell Lab of Ornithology | access-date=20 September 2024 }}</ref>

Two subspecies are recognised:<ref name=ioc/>
* ''S. n. ganongae'' ([[Ernst Mayr|Mayr]], 1935) – [[Ranongga]] (northwest [[New Georgia]] group, central west [[Solomon Islands]])
* ''S. n. nigrotectus'' ([[Ernst Hartert|Hartert, EJO]], 1908) – [[Vella Lavella]] (north [[New Georgia]] group, central west [[Solomon Islands]])

